Lab Architecture

Overview
This lab builds a network monitoring system that mirrors how enterprise infrastructure monitoring is designed with a dedicated monitoring zone, segmented networks, and zone-path awareness rather than just device-level monitoring.

The core design principle: monitor paths and zones, not just devices.

Physical layout

Everything runs as virtual machines on a single Windows host running VMware Workstation. The VMs are connected through VMware virtual networks (VMnets) that simulate real physical network segments.

